Algeria Lifts Its Emergency Law, State News Agency Reports

-- B y   A n d r e w   J .   B a r d e n
-- 
2011-02-25T01:56:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-25/algeria-lifts-its-emergency-law-state-news-agency-reports-1-.html
Algeria ended a long-standing state
of emergency, the official Algerian news agency reported today.  U.S. President  Barack Obama  said in a statement that the
step was a “positive sign” that the Algerian government is
heeding the will of its people.  “We look forward to additional steps by the government
that enable the Algerian people to fully exercise their
universal rights, including freedom of expression, association
and assembly,” Obama said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew J. Barden in Johannesburg at
 barden@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
